<br>
Neh'Ashirr drops not only the ORS and Epic Torch, but always has Key of Torsis.  She drops it everytime.  It's a No Rent key.  I always thought it was for some Iksar Necro quest (that's what Allakhazam says), but apparantly it works also to run the elevator in the back of CoM.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Key of Torsis from Neh will let you use that elevator</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
Of the 6 Reavers in CoM, one is the Lord Ghiosk Reaver just past the first locked door in the castle, the other famous one is the Neh'Ashirr Reaver at the very top (3rd house past the glass ramp), and 4 more are up the elevator behind the wall where the first Reaver is.  Until now, I thought a rogue had to operate that, but I saw a Shadow Knight use it today.<br>
<br>
If a mage binds at the top of CoM after a raid (and gets people up there with CotH who have Mez for the wandering mobs) you don't need a rogue to get to ALL the Black Reavers in the zone.   <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>That's powerful incentive to get your druid and ranger guild buddies to come running hehe</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Just get your guild to the top, get Neh (with key and maybe your Torch), then float down to the bottom of the glass ramp.  You don't need a rouge.  Just go on a raid and bind up past all the locked doors.<br>
<br>
This makes me wonder though, whether or not there are keys to the other doors in the zone.  Does anyone know or heard about it before?<br>
<br>
