<br>
Black Reavers with the 65 Earth pet were cake. I also have Suspend 2 so summon pet - 64 belt, fire weapons, mask of Mardu, Burnout V, flameshield of ro. Fight to the cortyard with no mobs under the walk through <br>
<br>
Suspend pet<br>
<br>
Get up to the walkway - bring pet back - kill the 2 wanderers making sure you dont get too close to either of the buildings.<br>
<br>
Kill the 2 mobs around Neh's house pulling them single with Malosini. There is also one mob in the house with the Black Reaver that makes an uncommon appearance at the door. Once these 3 mobs are dead - levi yourself and run around the outside of the house. This will agro the Black reaver - pull it back on the platform and kill it.<br>
<br>
Black Reavers are dead easy with 65 Earth Pet. The only issue is do not let your pet get out of melee with them. Your pet is a Mob as far as spell mechanics go. Black reavers blind.<br>
While your pet is in melee range of te reaver with its proc &quot;Blinding Fear&quot; the pet will continue wailing on it - but if the pet gets out of melee range it will run away as if feared. This is the way all Blind spells work on Mobs - just ask a pally.<br>
<br>
Ayways if you get arround this little issue Black reavers = cake and they dont seem to enrage.<br>
<br>
Once the reaver is dead Neh will spawn. Med up - its a good idea to have your best heal spell or 2 up for pet boy. When your ready to go rebuff Jobober and sick pet. Mala for good measure but I doubt you will get a chance to land a nuke on it - most of mine are resisted and I dont think I got 1 of my 10 sini's to land.<br>
<br>
I suggest knocking her off the platform - this is because she ends up in the cortyard with no mobs - down there you can push her arround to your hearts content - no problem. Up on the platform you have to be careful of such things as pushing her off with your Host of the Elements if you have it :P<br>
<br>
Spells that she liked to cast = Invoke Fear (on me a lot) so buff up that MR as much as you can. Complete heal - yes she complete heals once per fight - so just plan to kill her twice. Dispell (on me - annul) she seemed to think me having Kei on was cheating so she dispelled me on the first one I did - somewhat annoying - combat this with what junks you get and make sure kei is in slot 5 6 or 7 :P<br>
<br>
That said she really wasnt difficult - she doesnt enrage so dont freak out when she gets to low health.<br>
<br>
